00:06:24.340 --> 00:06:30.930
&gt;&gt; Paul Crego: Picture it,
Ikalto, a small village in Kakheti

00:06:30.930 --> 00:06:39.090
that is the eastern part of the
Georgian Soviet Socialist Republic.

00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:47.280
Saturday afternoon, July
7th, 1990, the church-- oops.

00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:51.590
There we go.

00:06:51.590 --> 00:06:57.070
The church of the transfiguration
[foreign language] also known

00:06:57.070 --> 00:07:02.280
as [foreign language], that
is Divinity of Godliness,

00:07:02.280 --> 00:07:07.560
among the surviving buildings of a
famous medieval theological school.

00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:12.640
Some of the great philosophical

00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:15.990
and literary figures had
studied here during the hay day

00:07:15.990 --> 00:07:21.440
of Georgia's Bagratid Dynasty
and its United Kingdom.

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:25.610
Not the least of it-- not the
least of these was the poet,

00:07:25.610 --> 00:07:29.790
Shota Rustavelli, author
of the epic poem,

00:07:29.790 --> 00:07:33.880
Vepkhist'q'aosani The
Knight in the Panther Skin.

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:41.920 position:56%
The inside of the church was in poor
repair, water stains were visible.

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:47.060
The frescoes had been whitewashed
likely during the imperial Russian

00:07:47.060 --> 00:07:52.760
period when some Georgian
churches had their Georgian

00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:56.130
identities erased.

00:07:56.130 --> 00:08:02.580
Icons of various styles had been
placed in a makeshift iconostasis.

00:08:02.580 --> 00:08:09.170
Boxes of sand in front of the
icons held thin beeswax candles,

00:08:09.170 --> 00:08:15.340
guttering in the soft,
warm, humid breeze.

00:08:15.340 --> 00:08:19.490
In response to a question asked
from among our group of students

00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:24.130
in Georgia for the first summer
school in Kartvelian studies

00:08:24.130 --> 00:08:28.410
at Tbilisi State University,
the intuitus [phonetic]

00:08:28.410 --> 00:08:32.890
or foreign tourists
service guide said

00:08:32.890 --> 00:08:36.950
that it was not a working church.

00:08:36.950 --> 00:08:39.290
Shortly after this
response, however,

00:08:39.290 --> 00:08:43.030
the church bells began to chime.

00:08:43.030 --> 00:08:46.870
And efficient to some
priestly order,

00:08:46.870 --> 00:08:51.580
who appeared as if he had
been waiting in the very wall

00:08:51.580 --> 00:08:57.740
of the church for his cue, placed
his service books on a lectern

00:08:57.740 --> 00:09:04.300
and began to chant what was likely
the vigil of the resurrection.

00:09:04.300 --> 00:09:08.930 position:56%
We wondered whether we had witnessed
the first service in the new life

00:09:08.930 --> 00:09:12.350
of this church of the
transfiguration.

00:09:12.350 --> 00:09:16.820
Certainly, it was among
the first and represented,

00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:22.330
iconified if you will the
transfiguration already well

00:09:22.330 --> 00:09:28.410
underway in the Georgian Orthodox
Church and in the Georgian nation.

00:09:28.410 --> 00:09:33.070
We were witnessing the
beginning of a remarkable new era

00:09:33.070 --> 00:09:39.670 position:56%
after nearly seven decades of
Soviet rule and its companion policy

00:09:39.670 --> 00:09:44.660 position:56%
of official state-sponsored atheism.

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:48.150
Although the Soviet Union did
not officially cease to exist

00:09:48.150 --> 00:09:54.400
until the end of 1991, there are
two dates before the official end

00:09:54.400 --> 00:10:00.550
that are essential starting points
for the concept of this paper.

00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:05.510
The first is December 25th, 1977.

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:10.960
The Orthodox Church in Georgia
uses what's called the Old Calendar

00:10:10.960 --> 00:10:16.020
so this is not Christmas,
but about two weeks before.

00:10:16.020 --> 00:10:20.390
This was the day when the
current Patriarch Catholicos

00:10:20.390 --> 00:10:25.770
of the Georgian Church,
Ilia II was enthroned.

00:10:25.770 --> 00:10:29.320
Although that sometime-- although
it was some difficult times early

00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:35.420
in his reign, these Catholicos,
Ilia II emerged in the 1980s

00:10:35.420 --> 00:10:39.120
as the leader who would begin
to revive the Orthodox Church

00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:45.040
in Georgia, he saw into a
future that held much promise

00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:47.260
for a renewed church

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:51.410
when independence would
come again to Georgia.

00:10:51.410 --> 00:10:59.430
The second date is April 9th, 1989.

00:10:59.430 --> 00:11:03.220
It was on an early Sunday morning
when Soviet troops attempting

00:11:03.220 --> 00:11:06.950
to disperse a demonstration
that had been developing

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:11.730
for several weeks fired
upon the crowd.

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:16.010
Nineteen people were
killed, among them 17 women

00:11:16.010 --> 00:11:19.380
and many more were injured.

00:11:19.380 --> 00:11:27.970
April 9th, 1989 was the day that
Soviet power died in Georgia.

00:11:27.970 --> 00:11:32.360
Huge funeral liturgies
soon became rallies

00:11:32.360 --> 00:11:35.640
for the resurrection of the nation.

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:39.440
Yes, there were political
structures that lingered

00:11:39.440 --> 00:11:43.640 position:56%
and the Communist Party shambled on.

00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:45.630
For the Georgian people however,

00:11:45.630 --> 00:11:50.560
communist rule was
body-hawking corpse

00:11:50.560 --> 00:11:55.630
that was left then
only further to decay.

00:11:55.630 --> 00:11:57.680
Within a year, there
was a box in front

00:11:57.680 --> 00:12:02.560
of the Supreme Soviet Building, now
Parliament, and near the memorial

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:05.860
for the victims of April 9th.

00:12:05.860 --> 00:12:09.530
And on this box, there was
an invitation for people

00:12:09.530 --> 00:12:15.810
to place their Communist cards
into the dustbin of history.

00:12:15.810 --> 00:12:21.220
In my brief time today, I
want to touch on a number

00:12:21.220 --> 00:12:26.490
of different topics, the growth
of the Orthodox Church in Georgia,

00:12:26.490 --> 00:12:32.150
church-state relations, the
Orthodox Church in society

00:12:32.150 --> 00:12:36.600 position:56%
and some publications of the church.

00:12:36.600 --> 00:12:41.330 position:56%
Let me pause at this point to thank
the African and Middle East Division

00:12:41.330 --> 00:12:47.050
for inviting me to speak today
particularly Dr. Mary-Jane Deeb,

00:12:47.050 --> 00:12:52.510
Chief, Joan Weeks, head of the Near
East Section and Dr. Levon Avdoyan,

00:12:52.510 --> 00:12:56.880
my reference colleague in
matters Armenian and Georgian.

00:12:56.880 --> 00:13:02.300
And if anyone wants to know, I have
been studying the Georgian language

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:05.990
since 1977 and a great deal

00:13:05.990 --> 00:13:08.900
of my research concerning
the Orthodox Church

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:14.910
in Georgia involves reading
Georgian language sources.

00:13:15.970 --> 00:13:20.670
The enthronement of Ilia
II as Catholicos Patriarch

00:13:20.670 --> 00:13:24.210
of the Orthodox Church
in Georgia marked a point

00:13:24.210 --> 00:13:27.920
after which this autocephalous
church began

00:13:27.920 --> 00:13:31.680
to experience a reversal
of its fortune.

00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:33.200
Although still in the time

00:13:33.200 --> 00:13:36.000
of Breshnev [assumed spelling]
conditions in Georgia,

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:41.110 position:56%
were more favorable than in some of
the other parts of the Soviet Union.

00:13:41.110 --> 00:13:47.710
They continued to improve during
the Gorbachev years of Glasnost.

00:13:47.710 --> 00:13:50.310
And there's Pearl Lenin
with his head bashed

00:13:50.310 --> 00:14:00.930 position:56%
in near the Natakhtari beer and soda
bottling plant, north of Mtskheta.

00:14:00.930 --> 00:14:05.250
And what was Lenin's Square
when I was still there

00:14:05.250 --> 00:14:11.180
in 1990 is now Freedom
Square with a statue topped

00:14:11.180 --> 00:14:16.210
by a golden St. George
slaying his dragon.

00:14:16.210 --> 00:14:19.880
Sadly, I missed Lenin coming
down by only about a week.

00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:25.700 position:56%
There had been rumors all summer and
we even got on the bus to go to free

00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:30.840
or well, Lenin Square at the time
to see it come down but we heard

00:14:30.840 --> 00:14:33.540
that the Georgians
forgotten ropes and such

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:37.720
by which to haul it down, anyway.

00:14:37.720 --> 00:14:40.740
One of the most important
early events for the future

00:14:40.740 --> 00:14:46.090 position:56%
of the church was the opening of the
Tbilisi Spiritual Academy in October

00:14:46.090 --> 00:14:53.000
in 1988 across from the
Zioni-- or Zion Cathedral.

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:56.230
This spiritual academy was
a companion to the seminary

00:14:56.230 --> 00:15:02.450
in Mtskheta that had sometimes
been open during the Soviet period.

00:15:02.450 --> 00:15:05.490
Before his enthronement,
Ilia II had been rector

00:15:05.490 --> 00:15:13.970 position:56%
of the Mtskheta Theological Seminary
from 1963 to 1972 and in 18--

00:15:13.970 --> 00:15:19.640
1989, the ancient autocephaly
or self-governing status

00:15:19.640 --> 00:15:23.900
of the Orthodox Church in
Georgia was officially recognized

00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:27.090
by the patriarch of Constantinople.

00:15:27.090 --> 00:15:34.050
The pace of change picked up in the
1990s and into the 21st century.

00:15:34.050 --> 00:15:41.970
At his enthronement in 1977, only
five eparchies existed in Georgia.

00:15:41.970 --> 00:15:45.360
There are now 50 including
seven outside

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:49.010
of the Republic of
Georgia's territory.

00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:51.810
The first years of the new
century saw a great deal

00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:56.410
of new church construction
and renovation.

00:15:56.410 --> 00:16:01.160
The numbers of working churches
has increased from probably no more

00:16:01.160 --> 00:16:07.170
than a couple of dozen
to over 850 by 2007.

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:12.110
We'll come back to that one.

00:16:12.110 --> 00:16:16.520
Political leaders got in on the
building, Eduard Shevardnadze

00:16:16.520 --> 00:16:21.810 position:56%
who became the head of state in
1992 and was later elected president

00:16:21.810 --> 00:16:27.060
after the 1995 Constitution
and served until the Revolution

00:16:27.060 --> 00:16:32.430
of the Roses in November of 2003,
sponsored the reconstruction

00:16:32.430 --> 00:16:34.370
of the Saint Nicholas Church

00:16:34.370 --> 00:16:40.170 position:56%
in the Narikala Fortress
overlooking the old part of Tbilisi.

00:16:40.170 --> 00:16:42.630
He was by the way baptized
Giorgi [assumed spelling]

00:16:42.630 --> 00:16:45.320
by the patriarch himself.

00:16:46.780 --> 00:16:50.650
From before 1990, the Orthodox
Church in Georgia had begun

00:16:50.650 --> 00:16:55.080
to make plans for the
construction of a new cathedral.

00:16:55.080 --> 00:16:59.280
It was to be called, "The
Cathedral of the Holy Trinity".

00:16:59.280 --> 00:17:05.200
A competition among architects was
held in 1990 but with the economy

00:17:05.200 --> 00:17:08.810
in ruins in the 1990s,
it became impossible

00:17:08.810 --> 00:17:12.760
to raise funds for
the new cathedral.

00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:16.330
Finally, in the opening
years of the 21st century,

00:17:16.330 --> 00:17:20.880
earnest construction began
with a large contribution

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:25.090
from Bidzina Ivanishvili,
who had made his money

00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:31.860
in Russia during the 1990s when
that country's economy was largely

00:17:31.860 --> 00:17:35.570
unfettered by regulation.

00:17:35.570 --> 00:17:39.890
This is the same Ivanishvili, who
became Prime Minister of Georgia

00:17:39.890 --> 00:17:44.830
after the Parliamentary
Elections of 2012.

00:17:44.830 --> 00:17:49.840
Churches were built in Tbilisi
and elsewhere, others repaired

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:58.330
and put back together literally
putting the stones back up in order

00:17:58.330 --> 00:18:02.830
for the churches again to exist.

00:18:02.830 --> 00:18:05.930
This included the church
of St. David the Builder

00:18:05.930 --> 00:18:10.240
who had been the ruler
of Georgia in its--

00:18:10.240 --> 00:18:17.480
in the Middle Ages when Georgia
was at its largest extent.

00:18:17.480 --> 00:18:22.880 position:56%
This church was built on the
grounds of Tbilisi State University.

00:18:22.880 --> 00:18:31.810 position:56%
Let's look a little at the Church
of the Holy Trinity as it was built.

00:18:33.690 --> 00:18:41.230
This was in late May or early
July 2000-- early June 2004.

00:18:41.230 --> 00:18:43.070
You can see some of
the ornamentation

00:18:43.070 --> 00:18:45.290
that was waiting to go up.

00:18:45.290 --> 00:18:50.070
Not all of the technology
was 21st century.

00:18:51.300 --> 00:18:54.280
This is an inside view
looking at the altar

00:18:54.280 --> 00:18:58.490
where the iconostasis
now is and up on the top

00:18:58.490 --> 00:19:03.360
