00:26:56.300 --> 00:27:00.110
So, a little bit about
church-state relations.

00:27:00.110 --> 00:27:03.850
As noted above, when the Republic
of Georgia emerged from the rubble

00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:07.430
of the Soviet Union as a
free and sovereign nation,

00:27:07.430 --> 00:27:12.460
the Orthodox Church found itself
in a new political context.

00:27:12.460 --> 00:27:15.860
After nearly seven decades
of militant and often crass

00:27:15.860 --> 00:27:20.300
and bullying, government-sponsored
official atheism,

00:27:20.300 --> 00:27:24.930
the Orthodox Church in Georgia
began again to exert its role

00:27:24.930 --> 00:27:30.060
as a foundational institution
in Georgian society.

00:27:30.060 --> 00:27:31.660
This foundation was supported

00:27:31.660 --> 00:27:37.430
by Georgia's first post-Soviet
president, Zviad Gamsakhurdia

00:27:37.430 --> 00:27:41.990
who ironically was driven from
power nearly at the same time

00:27:41.990 --> 00:27:45.860
that the Soviet Union
finally collapsed.

00:27:45.860 --> 00:27:51.150
He promoted a close relationship
with the Orthodox Church in part

00:27:51.150 --> 00:27:55.490
as a guarantor of the Georgian
nation and its freedom.

00:27:55.490 --> 00:27:59.470
In the political speeches, he
reminded his listeners that Georgia

00:27:59.470 --> 00:28:07.550 position:56%
as the lot, the word in Georgian is
[foreign language] of the Theotokos.

00:28:07.550 --> 00:28:09.360
This is a reference to the story

00:28:09.360 --> 00:28:13.780
that the apostles including the
Virgin Mary had divided missionary

00:28:13.780 --> 00:28:19.470
assignments up by casting
lots and Georgia fell to Mary.

00:28:19.470 --> 00:28:23.710
After a communication from her son
however, she came to understand

00:28:23.710 --> 00:28:27.080
that she would not be able
to fulfill this mission

00:28:27.080 --> 00:28:31.310
and Saint Andrew the
First-called took her place.

00:28:31.310 --> 00:28:34.750
This understanding of the
special protection of Georgia

00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:39.540
by the Theotokos became an
important theme for the church

00:28:39.540 --> 00:28:43.810
and its relationship to the nation.

00:28:43.810 --> 00:28:47.750
For the Orthodox Church in Georgia,
this has met not only a belief

00:28:47.750 --> 00:28:51.880
in her protection but
a severe responsibility

00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:58.670
to maintain the nation as worthy of
that protection in extreme cases.

00:28:58.670 --> 00:29:00.700
This is an issue for those who seek

00:29:00.700 --> 00:29:05.410
to rid the nation of
its impure others.

00:29:06.590 --> 00:29:11.540
Gamsakhurdia's support had
been a little more than ironic,

00:29:11.540 --> 00:29:18.030 position:56%
steep as he was in the belief system
of Rudolf Steiner's anthroposophy.

00:29:18.030 --> 00:29:22.950
Articles in the Orthodox churches
press attacking Steinerism appeared

00:29:22.950 --> 00:29:26.210
only years after Gamsakhurdia's
death.

00:29:26.210 --> 00:29:30.770
But it was clear that they
were kicking his corpse.

00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:36.750 position:56%
At first, the Republic of Georgia
operated under the 1921 Constitution

00:29:36.750 --> 00:29:39.360
of the Democratic Republic
of Georgia

00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:43.630
that had codified a
separation of church and state,

00:29:43.630 --> 00:29:48.480
already in existence from the
early days of that republic,

00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:51.300
a separation that have
actually been more separate

00:29:51.300 --> 00:29:54.580
than the church had desired.

00:29:54.580 --> 00:29:59.650
Georgia adopted a new
constitution in 1995 several years

00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:03.490
after Shevardnadze
had returned to power.

00:30:03.490 --> 00:30:07.370
This constitution enshrined
the Orthodox Church

00:30:07.370 --> 00:30:12.610
as the first among equals,
freedom of religion is guaranteed,

00:30:12.610 --> 00:30:15.250
but the constitution also speaks

00:30:15.250 --> 00:30:20.810
of the historical precedence
of orthodoxy in Georgia.

00:30:20.810 --> 00:30:24.880
No other religion or Christian
denomination is mentioned

00:30:24.880 --> 00:30:29.430
as having this sort of
historical relevance.

00:30:29.430 --> 00:30:34.340
Article 9 of the Constitution
as amended reads,

00:30:34.340 --> 00:30:39.820
"The state proclaims the full
freedom of belief and confession

00:30:39.820 --> 00:30:45.690
at the same time, acknowledging the
special role Georgia's apostolic

00:30:45.690 --> 00:30:50.950
autocephalous Orthodox Church
has played in Georgia's history

00:30:50.950 --> 00:30:58.310
and its-- and also recognizes
its independence from the state.

00:30:58.310 --> 00:31:01.230
The relationship of Georgia's state

00:31:01.230 --> 00:31:07.150
and Georgia's apostolic
autocephalous Orthodox Church is

00:31:07.150 --> 00:31:12.180
to be defined by a
constitutional concordat.

00:31:12.180 --> 00:31:15.170
The constitutional concordant--

00:31:15.170 --> 00:31:18.740
concordat is to be
consistent in general

00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:23.590
with all internationally-recognized
principles and norms,

00:31:23.590 --> 00:31:28.680
specifically in the sphere
of fundamental human rights.

00:31:28.680 --> 00:31:33.320
This constitutionally-mandated
concordat between the government

00:31:33.320 --> 00:31:37.400
and the church was eventually
signed on October 14th,

00:31:37.400 --> 00:31:44.060
2002 by President Shevardnadze
and Patriarch Catholicos Ilia II

00:31:44.060 --> 00:31:48.020
at the Church of the
Living pillar Svetitskhoveli

00:31:48.020 --> 00:31:51.570 position:56%
in the old capital city of Mtskheta.

00:31:51.570 --> 00:31:55.780 position:56%
This document provided details for
the relationship of church and state

00:31:55.780 --> 00:32:02.350 position:56%
in Georgia and ratified its primary
status above other religious groups,

00:32:02.350 --> 00:32:07.930 position:56%
specifically the special status of
the church, included tax exemptions,

00:32:07.930 --> 00:32:11.410
clerical release from
military service

00:32:11.410 --> 00:32:15.860
and a special legal
status for the patriarch.

00:32:15.860 --> 00:32:21.260
A commentary on the concordat,
its title translated into English,

00:32:21.260 --> 00:32:25.720
Commentaries on the Constitutional
Concordat between the Government

00:32:25.720 --> 00:32:31.910
of Georgia and Georgia's Apostolic
Autocephalous Orthodox Church,

00:32:31.910 --> 00:32:36.000
was written by Davit Cikvaize.

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:40.490
He promoted the idea that the
concordat have made the Orthodox

00:32:40.490 --> 00:32:44.700
Church in Georgia the
official state church.

00:32:44.700 --> 00:32:47.370
While, I do not believe
this is technically

00:32:47.370 --> 00:32:50.600
so the Orthodox Church
is often operated

00:32:50.600 --> 00:32:53.980
as though it had been made such.

00:32:53.980 --> 00:32:57.980
This is especially noted in
its reported interference

00:32:57.980 --> 00:33:04.610
in the property rights of other
churches and religious communities.

00:33:04.610 --> 00:33:08.410
The ambiguity concerning the
status of other religions

00:33:08.410 --> 00:33:12.660
and other Christian denominations
was somewhat nearly rated

00:33:12.660 --> 00:33:18.710
with the religious law that
came into effect in July 2012.

00:33:18.710 --> 00:33:20.010
The first two readings

00:33:20.010 --> 00:33:24.110
of this legislation had
included only what was referred

00:33:24.110 --> 00:33:29.800
to in some documents as the seven
historic religious communities,

00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:35.540
orthodoxy, Catholicism, the
Lutherans, Baptists, Jews, Muslims

00:33:35.540 --> 00:33:39.540
and the Armenian Apostolic Church.

00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:42.140
Jews have been present in Georgia

00:33:42.140 --> 00:33:46.170
and other South Caucasian
territories since early

00:33:46.170 --> 00:33:49.740
after the Babylonian captivity.

00:33:49.740 --> 00:33:55.720 position:56%
Muslims, since the second generation
after Mohammed and Armenian

00:33:55.720 --> 00:34:01.190
and Georgian Christians have lived
intermingled since the early days

00:34:01.190 --> 00:34:05.220
of Christianity in
the South Caucasus.

00:34:05.220 --> 00:34:10.710
Catholic missionaries were present
in Georgia in medieval times.

00:34:10.710 --> 00:34:15.570
Baptists and Lutherans have been
present since the 19th century

00:34:15.570 --> 00:34:18.410
and as a result of
religious movements coming

00:34:18.410 --> 00:34:22.030
by way of the Russian empire.

00:34:22.030 --> 00:34:25.640
In between the second and
third readings of the 2012 Law,

00:34:25.640 --> 00:34:30.370
the Committee on European
Integration widely expanded the

00:34:30.370 --> 00:34:33.260
number of religious
communities to conform

00:34:33.260 --> 00:34:37.130
to those recognized by
the European Council.

00:34:37.130 --> 00:34:41.000
The Orthodox Church had not
been consulted on this change

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:46.620
and reacted adversely to the
broad expansion of the new law.

00:34:46.620 --> 00:34:50.350
After some reconsiderations
of its public stance,

00:34:50.350 --> 00:34:53.080
the Senate of the Orthodox
Church in Georgia backed

00:34:53.080 --> 00:34:57.310
down from its most severe
criticism of the new law.

00:34:57.310 --> 00:35:01.080
At this point, the church
seemed to have realized

00:35:01.080 --> 00:35:05.530
that its overreach was
leading to bad publicity,

00:35:05.530 --> 00:35:08.930
not only in Georgia
but around the world.

00:35:08.930 --> 00:35:11.630
At the same time, the
Senate insisted

00:35:11.630 --> 00:35:14.350
that the parliament
should consult with it

00:35:14.350 --> 00:35:18.650
when laws affecting religion
were under consideration.

00:35:19.990 --> 00:35:23.970
There is generally an ongoing
in complex relationship

00:35:23.970 --> 00:35:27.860
of the Orthodox Church in
Georgia with not only its place

00:35:27.860 --> 00:35:31.800
in the nation, but also its
relationship with the government

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:36.650
that promotes a European or a
Western orientation complete

00:35:36.650 --> 00:35:40.670
with the promotion of
civil and human rights.

00:35:40.670 --> 00:35:45.800
The Orthodox Church in this time
of independence has been anxious

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:51.200
about the way in which they
understand how freedom can quickly

00:35:51.200 --> 00:35:54.420
become a free for all sort

00:35:54.420 --> 00:36:01.130
of attitude toward
ethical and moral norms.

00:36:01.130 --> 00:36:04.610
There is no question that the
Orthodox Church is the most

00:36:04.610 --> 00:36:08.190
respected institution
in Georgian society

00:36:08.190 --> 00:36:13.660
and that Patriarch Catholicos Ilia
II is the most respected individual

00:36:13.660 --> 00:36:16.580
in the Republic of Georgia.

00:36:16.580 --> 00:36:19.490
This has been so for
most of the years

00:36:19.490 --> 00:36:22.650
since Georgia regained
its independence.

00:36:22.650 --> 00:36:26.970 position:56%
It is as much so now as the campaign

00:36:26.970 --> 00:36:31.780 position:56%
for the October Parliamentary
Elections have revealed a widespread

00:36:31.780 --> 00:36:36.210
disdain for many of the political
parties and coalitions currently

00:36:36.210 --> 00:36:38.580
in the Georgian Parliament.

00:36:39.740 --> 00:36:43.980
On the other hand, it has been
difficult for the Orthodox Church

00:36:43.980 --> 00:36:50.490
as for churches of many sorts
in post-Soviet states to adjust

00:36:50.490 --> 00:36:55.110
to the new social and political
realities of the late 20th

00:36:55.110 --> 00:36:58.320
and early 21st centuries.

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:02.100
The effect of seven decades
of Soviet rule on Georgia,

00:37:02.100 --> 00:37:04.720
in the Georgia on the
Orthodox Church

00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:10.580
and other religious communities
cannot be overestimated.

00:37:10.580 --> 00:37:14.480
Once of the historical developments
or better, non-developments

00:37:14.480 --> 00:37:19.250
of the Orthodox churches in
Soviet time and space was

00:37:19.250 --> 00:37:24.100
that it prevented these communities
from the sort of modern discussion

00:37:24.100 --> 00:37:28.860
and debates that characterized
Christianity in other parts

00:37:28.860 --> 00:37:31.930
of the world in that century.

00:37:31.930 --> 00:37:36.050
In the few churches that
survived the Communist regime,

00:37:36.050 --> 00:37:42.090
liturgy was preserved but talk of
modernizing liturgical language

00:37:42.090 --> 00:37:45.420
or the education of
faithful or involvement

00:37:45.420 --> 00:37:48.690
in social activities was forbidden.

00:37:48.690 --> 00:37:54.680
After the fall of the Soviet Union,
the Orthodox Church in Georgia,

00:37:54.680 --> 00:37:59.800 position:56%
in response to the dire economic and
social needs of the Georgian people,

00:37:59.800 --> 00:38:04.140
became involved again
in the social sphere.

00:38:04.140 --> 00:38:09.380
Since 1994, the church's Lazarus
Foundation has been a mainstay

00:38:09.380 --> 00:38:12.700
of large-scale relief
work in society.

00:38:12.700 --> 00:38:17.160
One of the more difficult
adjustments

00:38:17.160 --> 00:38:21.860
in this new time has
involved ecumenical relations.

00:38:21.860 --> 00:38:25.730
For a time, the church in Georgia
played a role, if only a small one

00:38:25.730 --> 00:38:28.960
in the global ecumenical movement.

00:38:28.960 --> 00:38:34.990
Ilia II was for time a president
of the World Council of Churches.

00:38:34.990 --> 00:38:38.300
While this title did not mean
that he was involved in the day

00:38:38.300 --> 00:38:43.970
to day operations of the council,
the position was a recognition

00:38:43.970 --> 00:38:48.380
of Ilia II's important
and the revival of post--

00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:51.870
of the churches in
post-Soviet space.

00:38:51.870 --> 00:38:58.510
In the 1990s, the Orthodox churches
in general and the Orthodox Church

00:38:58.510 --> 00:39:01.830
in Georgia in particular,
began more closely

00:39:01.830 --> 00:39:08.400
to assess their participation in
dialog with other Christian bodies.

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:12.890
Some of the non-canonical churches
calling themselves Orthodox had

00:39:12.890 --> 00:39:18.470
proclaimed ecumenism a heresy and
this notion began to be expressed

00:39:18.470 --> 00:39:27.720 position:56%
in all parts of orthodoxy including
Georgia's two non-canonical Orthodox

00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:31.920
churches that have
existed in Georgia.

00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:37.590
One of them styled at first as the
true Orthodox Church of Georgia,

00:39:37.590 --> 00:39:42.120
was under the authority of--
the Metropolitan of Boston.

00:39:42.120 --> 00:39:45.680
Yes, Boston, Massachusetts,
at the Monastery

00:39:45.680 --> 00:39:50.700
of the Holy Transfiguration
in Brooklyn, Massachusetts.

00:39:50.700 --> 00:39:55.690
The other was led-- the other was
a small group led by the violent

00:39:55.690 --> 00:40:00.120
and notorious Father
Basil Mkalavishvili

00:40:00.120 --> 00:40:04.820
and under the authority of a
Schismatic Greek Church known

00:40:04.820 --> 00:40:08.640
as the Synod of Resistance.

00:40:08.640 --> 00:40:14.180
Some of the monks of the Orthodox
Church were also almost in schism

00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:18.670
from the main church over
the issue of ecumenism.

00:40:18.670 --> 00:40:23.010
Their influence was part of
the Georgian church's decision

00:40:23.010 --> 00:40:27.120
to leave both the World Council
of Churches and the Conference

00:40:27.120 --> 00:40:32.720
of European Churches in 1997.

00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:37.670
Officially, the Georgian Synod
cited that, "World Council

00:40:37.670 --> 00:40:42.220
of Churches leaderships continued
efforts to endow the organization

00:40:42.220 --> 00:40:48.180
with unified ecclesiological
functions", and the WCC's alleged

00:40:48.180 --> 00:40:55.690
"failure to take interests of the
Orthodox Church fully into account"

00:40:55.690 --> 00:40:58.530
as reasons for their action.

00:40:58.530 --> 00:41:01.840
Many of the anti-ecumenical
monks were disciplined

00:41:01.840 --> 00:41:04.910
for their rebellion
despite the fact that some

00:41:04.910 --> 00:41:08.870
of their agenda was enacted
and has remained the position

00:41:08.870 --> 00:41:13.250
of the Orthodox Church
in Georgia ever since.

00:41:13.250 --> 00:41:18.850
As an example of this in
the preliminary meetings

00:41:18.850 --> 00:41:22.800
of the Orthodox churches
for the Holy and Great Synod

00:41:22.800 --> 00:41:27.490
of the Orthodox Church
soon to take place on Crete

00:41:27.490 --> 00:41:32.660 position:56%
and in subsequent articles, Georgian
authors have been very critical

00:41:32.660 --> 00:41:36.490
of any ongoing dialog
with other communities

00:41:36.490 --> 00:41:39.200
who call themselves Christian.

00:41:39.200 --> 00:41:42.880
Their first point and
really their only point is

00:41:42.880 --> 00:41:49.220
that there can only be one holy
Catholic and Apostolic church

00:41:49.220 --> 00:41:54.370
and that all the heterodox
are therefore not the church.

00:41:54.370 --> 00:42:00.560
They have also encouraged the
designation of ecumenism as heresy.

00:42:00.560 --> 00:42:04.210
This of course has
also repercussions

00:42:04.210 --> 00:42:08.370
in how the Orthodox Church
deals with the other Christians

00:42:08.370 --> 00:42:13.390
and non-Christians in
the Republic of Georgia.

00:42:13.390 --> 00:42:18.860 position:56%
One of my sources said well, they're
actually doing business for Moscow,

00:42:18.860 --> 00:42:20.650
the Moscow Patriarchate

00:42:20.650 --> 00:42:26.010
and the Russian church while
the Russian church can look--

00:42:26.010 --> 00:42:32.350
can have its hands clean from
disrupting the Great Synod.

00:42:32.350 --> 00:42:34.850
Another large conflict
of the Orthodox Church

00:42:34.850 --> 00:42:39.680
in Georgia has involved a
small LGBT community there.

00:42:39.680 --> 00:42:44.600
This conflict came to a
head on May 17, 21013.

00:42:44.600 --> 00:42:48.150
A small group of demonstrators,
only a couple of dozen

00:42:48.150 --> 00:42:50.880
at the most had gathered in Tbilisi

00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:55.770
to observe the international
day against homophobia.

00:42:55.770 --> 00:43:02.030
They were besieged by a huge
counterdemonstration led

00:43:02.030 --> 00:43:06.370
by Orthodox priests
all of whom priests

00:43:06.370 --> 00:43:10.080
and other demonstrators
were breathing violence

00:43:10.080 --> 00:43:12.660
against the first group.

00:43:12.660 --> 00:43:16.830
Those observing the Idaho
Day as its called fearing

00:43:16.830 --> 00:43:22.980
for their very lives were
hustled on to buses by police.

00:43:22.980 --> 00:43:28.990
The Orthodox Church has since named
the 17th of May to be Family Day.

00:43:28.990 --> 00:43:32.540
This year, it was observed by the
presence of the World Congress

00:43:32.540 --> 00:43:37.760
of Families, a group founded
in the United States encouraged

00:43:37.760 --> 00:43:43.680
by official Russia and a group that
has been designated a hate group

00:43:43.680 --> 00:43:47.160
by the Southern Poverty Law Center.

00:43:47.160 --> 00:43:53.500
